      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> [4 tbsp] </span>tbsp <strong>olive oil </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek</strong> and cook for 4 min until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
